      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Numerous studies have explored the effects of minimum wage hikes on small businesses and local economies. Research suggests that, in many cases, small businesses like yours may indeed experience reduced hours, increased prices, or even closures as a direct result of higher labor costs. A 2019 study by the University of California, Berkeley, found associations between minimum wage increases and job losses for low-wage workers, particularly in retail and food service sectors.",
      "source": "target",
